          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">General Assembly calls for a ceasefire</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-13-2.jpg" alt="General Assembly calls for a ceasefire" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The U.N. General Assembly overwhelmingly <a href="https://press.un.org/en/2024/ga12667.doc.htm" target="_blank">passed</a> two resolutions: one calling for an immediate ceasefire in Gaza and the other supporting the U.N. agency for Palestinian refugees, UNRWA, which Israel has sought to ban. The resolution demanding a ceasefire was approved by a vote of 158-9, with 13 abstentions, while the resolution backing UNRWA passed with 159 votes in favor, nine against, and 11 abstentions. The United States voted against both resolutions, <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/un-general-assembly-passes-resolution-on-gaza-ceasefire/a-71029784" target="_blank">citing</a> these resolutions don’t do much to combat Hamas and are counterproductive.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The Israeli ambassador to the UN said it was all about appeasement. Those for the <a href="https://apnews.com/article/un-gaza-unrwa-palestinians-israel-resolutions-vote-2df5701e79b9678104e60a99b17d2f7a" target="_blank">resolutions</a> vented their resentment and brought up the massive death toll in Gaza. The resolutions were passed despite the US having a permanent veto because this only applies to decisions made by the Security Council.​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
