        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Venezuela-Argentina diplomatic spat</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Argentina and Venezuela are in a <a href="https://apnews.com/article/venezuela-maduro-opposition-argentina-embassy-asylum-milei-ca1e1132a10bed21b2af94f94c406b5e" target="_blank">diplomatic row</a> over six Venezuelan opposition members currently housed in the Argentine embassy in Caracas. These people sought asylum after Venezuelan authorities issued arrest warrants accusing them of inciting violence. Argentina alleges that Venezuela has cut water and power to the diplomatic headquarters, restricted food supplies, and stationed security forces nearby who are doing what they can to harass them. Argentina says this isn’t acceptable and demands safe passage for the asylum seekers.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Venezuela and Argentina have been ideological enemies for the past year since the current Argentine president, Javier Meilei, was elected at the end of 2023. Both countries issued <a href="https://www.firstpost.com/world/maduro-vs-milei-courts-in-argentina-venezuela-issue-arrest-orders-for-each-others-presidents-13818431.html" target="_blank">arrest warrants</a> for the other leader earlier this year and have had a series of tit-for-tat measures against each other. </p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>

