          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇷🇴 Romania and Bulgaria:</strong>    
          Bulgaria and Romania will be upgraded to <a href="https://www.euronews.com/my-europe/2024/12/12/romania-and-bulgaria-are-granted-full-schengen-membership-with-one-caveat#:~:text=Romania%20and%20Bulgaria%20will%20become%20full%2Dtime%20members%20of%20the,both%20countries%20ready%20to%20join." target="_blank">full Schengen membership</a> as of January 1st, 2025. This is a process that has been a decade in the making. Both countries were granted partial membership this year, where arrivals by air and sea were no longer checked. Austria was the last remaining member to give the green light to this decision. The two countries must comply with the Budapest agreement, which introduces checks at the land borders between Hungary and Romania and between Romania and Bulgaria for "at least" six months.</p>
        </mj-text>
