        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇫🇷 France:</strong>   
          French President Emmanuel Macron returned early from a trip to Poland and is set to <a href="https://www.lemonde.fr/en/france/article/2024/12/12/macron-to-name-france-s-new-prime-minister-on-friday_6736003_7.html" target="_blank">announce</a> France’s new prime minister today, according to a statement from the Elysée Palace. This follows a week of political turbulence after former Prime Minister Michel Barnier’s government was ousted in a <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/2024/12/04/europe/france-no-confidence-vote-barnier-crisis-intl/index.html" target="_blank">no-confidence vote</a>, leaving a caretaker administration to manage key legislative matters. The appointment of a new prime minister is critical to stabilizing Macron’s administration as he seeks to build consensus amid fractured political alignments. This is a tall order, as France has a strong far right-wing and left-wing <a href="https://www.lemonde.fr/en/france/article/2024/07/07/french-elections-left-projected-to-win-most-seats-ahead-of-macron-s-coalition-and-far-right_6676978_7.html#:~:text=France%27s%20left-wing%20parties%20won%20the%20most%20seats%20in,President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%27s%20coalition%20and%20well%20below%20expectations." target="_blank">presence</a> within the government that opposes many policies. Macron’s ally François Bayrou was tipped as a <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cx27wp35j5jo" target="_blank">possible choice</a> for prime minister. Bayrou is a former justice minister acquitted this year of embezzling EU funds.</p>
        </mj-text>
