          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">What is Liberland?</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-13-3.jpg" alt="What is Liberland?" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><a href="https://liberland.org/news/476-visiting-liberland-how-to-currently-get-to-the-land" target="_blank">Liberland</a> is a self-declared micronation located on a disputed plot of land between Croatia and Serbia along the Danube River. Founded in 2015 by Czech politician <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-37941931" target="_blank">Vít Jedlicka</a>, it was proclaimed a free republic. The area in question, Gornja Siga, was left unclaimed following border agreements between Croatia and Serbia in the 1990s. This resulted in its status as terra nullius—land no country officially claims. </p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Croatia and Serbia did not recognize Liberland's declaration of independence, and both countries have attempted to prevent people from settling in the area. Despite this, Liberland has <a href="https://liberland.team/" target="_blank">attracted</a> individuals interested in its libertarian ideals, which include minimal government, personal freedoms, and low taxes. The micronation has created its own flag, <a href="https://liberland.org/constitution" target="_blank">constitution</a>, and <a href="https://docs.liberland.org/" target="_blank">government structure</a>. However, due to ongoing territorial disputes and a need for international recognition, it primarily exists as an online movement with little physical presence.​</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
